main event: A disc-shaped object was observed traveling at high speed over Phoenix, Arizona.
interesting points: The object was described as large, with a diameter of 75-80 ft and a height of 15-20 ft.,It traveled at high speed, accelerated rapidly, and changed direction during observation.,The observation lasted for 10 minutes with 3 confirmed witnesses.,The sighting was reported to potentially be a balloon but ruled out other explanations such as meteor or comet.,Visibility in the area was noted to be sixty miles with clear skies.
witness description: witnesses included individuals observing the object from different locations in Phoenix
